	"GPIO": {
		"description": "General purpose input/output pins with internal pull-up resistors selectable. They are tri-stated when a reset condition becomes active, even if the clock is not running. External (INT0..1) and pin change (PCI0..2) interrupt requests. The external interrupts can be triggered by a falling or rising edge or a low level. PCI0 will trigger if any enabled PCINT[0:7] pin toggles, PCI1 will trigger if any enabled PCINT[8:14] pin toggles, and PCI2 will trigger if any enabled PCINT[16:23] pin toggles. The interrupts will trigger even for pins configured as outputs.",
